com.artemis.injection

Class FieldHandler

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.artemis.injection.FieldHandler

  • public class FieldHandler
extends Object
    FieldHandler provides dependency-values to an Injector by sequentially iterating over a list of registered FieldResolver.

    The method resolve(Class, Field) will return the first non-null value provided by FieldResolver.resolve(Class, Field), or null if no resolver returned a valid value.

    During World construction, after systems and managers have been created, #initialize(World) will be called for each registered FieldResolver

    If FieldResolver implements UseInjectionCache, UseInjectionCache.setCache(InjectionCache) will be called prior to FieldResolver.initialize(World) being called, availing the InjectionCache used by this handler.

    Author:
    Snorre E. Brekke

    • Constructor Detail

      • FieldHandler

        public FieldHandler(InjectionCache cache,
            Bag<FieldResolver> fieldResolvers)
        Constructs a new FieldHandler with the provided fieldResolvers. This constructor should be used when full control over the FieldResolver order is required.

        For Artemis to function correctly, ArtemisFieldResolver should be added somewhere in the bag, or added via addFieldResolver(FieldResolver) prior to world construction.

        Parameters:
        cache - used for better reflection-speed.
        fieldResolvers - bag of fieldresolver this FieldHandler should use.
        See Also:
        ArtemisFieldResolver

      • FieldHandler

        public FieldHandler(InjectionCache cache)
        Constructs a ned FieldHandler with an ArtemisFieldResolver and WiredFieldResolver already registered, which can resolve ComponentMapper, BaseSystem and Manager types registered in the World Wire.
        Parameters:
        cache - used for better reflection-speed.
        See Also:
        ArtemisFieldResolver

    • Method Detail

      • initialize

        public void initialize(World world,
              Map<String,Object> injectables)
        During World construction, after systems and managers have been created, #initialize(World) will be called for each registered FieldResolver

        If FieldResolver implements UseInjectionCache, UseInjectionCache.setCache(InjectionCache) will be called prior to FieldResolver.initialize(World) being called, availing the InjectionCache used by this handler.

        Parameters:
        world - the world this FieldHandler is being used for
        Throws:
        WorldConfigurationException - when injector has no way to deal with injectables.

      • resolve

        public Object resolve(Class<?> fieldType,
             Field field)
        Returns the first non-null value provided by FieldResolver.resolve(Class, Field), or null if no resolver returned a valid value.
        Parameters:
        fieldType - class of the field
        field - field for which a value should be resolved
        Returns:
        a non-null value if any FieldResolver could provide an instance for the field, null if the field could not be resolved

      • addFieldResolver

        public final void addFieldResolver(FieldResolver fieldResolver)
        Adds a FieldResolver to this handler. Resolvers added first, will be used first for resolving fields, so the order of add operations is significant.
        Parameters:
        fieldResolver - is added to this FieldHandler fieldresolver-list
